# Allowlist policy: block everything, then re-include the small set the
# Dockerfile actually COPYs. Keeps `docker build .` from shipping 250+ MB
# of .venv / .git / caches to the daemon and prevents accidental bloat
# when new top-level files appear.
#
# If you add a new COPY in docker/Dockerfile, mirror it with a `!` line
# below.

**

# Project metadata + license consumed by the builder stage.
!pyproject.toml
!uv.lock
!README.md
!LICENSE

# The package source tree.
!src
!src/**

# Re-exclude noise that may live inside src/ but never belongs in the image.
src/**/__pycache__
src/**/*.py[cod]
src/**/*.egg-info
